    "body": "Are you referring to the [sendrawtransaction](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/internal/ethapi/api.go#L1700) in internal/ethapi? If so, then the function (i believe) is only for interfacing with the local node, which isn't broadcasted to other nodes. If you want to learn about broadcasting to other nodes, have a look around the RPC and P2P modules - see the [RCP call function](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/rpc/client.go#L282) or [P2P messages](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/p2p/message.go#L99). \r\n\r\nHow you communicate with other nodes will depend largely on what sort of client you're running (or not) and where the message is going/coming from. ",
